CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 19, 1941, pg. 23, reads: "Prizewinner In Show - Ernestine Holloway, first prize winner in Metropolitan Baptist church Hair Style show which was held last Tuesday evening. Miss Holloway was the Princess Beauty Shop model, Lola Sanders, operator and proprietor, at 1601 Wylie Avenue."
TitMainTitle: Three quarter portrait of Ernestine Holloway wearing dark sailor dress with eagle patch on short sleeve, posed in front of dark background, in Harris Studio
